1. Preheat the oven to 425Â°F. Arrange the peppers, cut-side up, on an oiled baking dish to fit. Brush the peppers with some oil. 2. Place 4 garlic slices in each pepper. Place 4 red cherry tomatoes in each yellow-pepper half and 4 yellow cherry tomatoes in each red pepper half. Sprinkle the peppers evenly with the capers, thyme, salt and pepper. Drizzle with the remaining olive oil. Bake for 35 minutes. Cool the peppers to room temperature. 3. To serve, arrange the peppers on a platter in alternating colors.